.TH ABRAFLEXI-MATCHER-NEW2OLD 1 "July 17, 2026" "abraflexi-matcher" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
abraflexi-matcher-new2old \- Match incoming payments day by day, newest to oldest, in AbraFlexi
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B abraflexi-matcher-new2old
[OPTIONS]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B abraflexi-matcher-new2old
matches unpaid issued invoices against incoming payments, walking backward
day by day from today toward
.BR MATCHER_DAYS_BACK
days ago (defaulting to the number of days elapsed so far this year). It
is intended for catching up a backlog where the most recent payments are
the most valuable to reconcile first.
.SH OPTIONS
This script uses environment variables for configuration.
.TP
.B RESULT_FILE
Path to the output JSON report file.
.TP
.B MATCHER_DAYS_BACK
Number of days to look back for payments (default: elapsed days of the current year)
.TP
.B MATCHER_LOCALIZE
Locale for log/report messages: en_US (default), cs_CZ, or sk_SK.
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_OVERPAY
Document type code used to automatically settle overpayments; empty (default) = do not settle overpayments automatically.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
The script requires AbraFlexi connection details:
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_URL
AbraFlexi server URL
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_LOGIN
AbraFlexi login username
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_PASSWORD
AbraFlexi password
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_COMPANY
AbraFlexi company code
.SH FILES
.TP
.I match_report.json
Default output file containing the matching results in JSON format compliant with the multiflexi report schema.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR abraflexi-matcher (1),
.BR abraflexi-matcher-out (1),
.BR abraflexi-match-varsym (1),
.BR abraflexi-match-specsym (1),
.BR abraflexi-match-accountno (1)
